result.name: Ying Vegetarian

reviews.text: Wonderful vegetarian food in Asian style, not as plain as that Buddha style. A bit commercial oriented. Try a bit before you really like it as it's more like a snack than a regular meal in volume. It's far more heavy in oil content than expected. Good to have a try. New experience.

I love the idea of trying Chinese cuisine where I can safely order anything I want not having to worry about whether there is some meat in it or not. Funny that all the names do have the names of the meats/fish and you have no idea what the dish is made of (mostly soy, I think ...) Nice!

It's good restaurant for vegetarians who want to try local Chinese food. Name from the menu may look if its non vegetarian food but those are just fake names given. So vegetarian can have their local food trial over here without worry. There is no desert in the menu, which I feel should be added.

Really enjoyable and delicious vegetarian food,  kids and us totally enjoyed ourselves, a surprising find indeed!

Set lunch at HK$45 comes with nice hot soup.
Beautiful and lovely thank you so mucc
